===Etymology===
From {{etyl|fr|en}} {{m|fr|épilogue}}, from {{etyl|la|en}} {{m|la|epilogus}}, from {{etyl|grc|en}} {{m|grc|ἐπίλογος||a conclusion, peroration of a speech, epilogue of a play}}, from {{m|grc|ἐπιλέγειν||say in addition}}, from {{m|grc|ἐπί||in addition}} + {{m|grc|λέγειν||to say}}.

===Pronunciation===
* {{a|RP}} {{IPA|/ˈɛp.ɪ.lɒɡ/|lang=en}}
* {{a|US}} {{IPA|/ˈɛpɪlɔɡ/|lang=en}}
* {{a|US|cot-caught|Canada}} {{IPA|/ˈɛpɪlɑɡ/|lang=en}}

===Noun===
{{wikipedia}}
{{en-noun}}

# A short [[speech]], [[spoken]] [[directly]] at the [[audience]] at the end of a [[play]]
# The [[performer]] who gives this speech
# A brief [[oration]] or [[script]] at the end of a [[literary]] [[piece]]; an [[afterword]]
# {{label|en|computing}} A component of a [[computer program]] that prepares the computer to return from a [[routine]].

